                <head>No. 115.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Evarts</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Osborn</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-04-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 13, 1880</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 87.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No.
                    132, in which you inclose a copy of a note from the Chilian Minister of Foreign
                    Affairs, soliciting the friendly offices of the legations of the United States
                    at La Paz and Santiago, in securing an exchange of prisoners of war between
                    Chili and Bolivia, and to say in reply that Mr. Adams, who succeeds Mr. Pettis
                    in the mission to Bolivia, presently departs for his post at La Paz and will be
                    instructed in the direction desired. The person in charge of the archives of the
                    legation at La Paz is not authorized to act in a diplomatic sense.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WM. M. EVARTS.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
